{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"broody-bundle-giant","description":"# BUG: code-review vote renders a fail-closed DET detector match as \"BLOCK — finding / 0 blocking issues\"\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. Push a change touching a file that a fail-closed DET detector (gitleaks secret-detection) matches on.\n2. The 4-pass LLM gate returns PASS (no LLM blocking findings), but apply_failclosed forces BLOCK.\n3. The Gerrit vote is LLM-Review-1 tagged \"[LLM-Review: BLOCK — finding]\" with message \"rebar code review found 0 blocking issue(s):\" — and NO robot comment names the match.\n\nRoot cause: src/rebar/llm/code_review/detectors.py:123-151 apply_failclosed sets\nverdict[\"verdict\"]=\"BLOCK\" on a match but never appends the match to verdict[\"blocking\"]\n(it only records it under coverage.security_detectors). review_bot/adapter.py then counts\nlen(verdict[\"blocking\"])==0 and renders \"found 0 blocking issue(s)\"; adapter.py:183-191 tags\nit \"finding\". voter.py posts only the message. So a genuine detector block is unnamed and\nnon-actionable — and a REAL leaked secret is hidden from the author identically.\n\nExpected: a fail-closed detector match is surfaced as a named, counted blocking finding.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] apply_failclosed appends a kernel-shaped finding (criterion + file + remediation hint) to verdict[\"blocking\"] when blocking_enabled and there is a match; the finalize invariant holds.\n- [ ] Gerrit message reads \"found N blocking issue(s):\" (N>=1) and names the match; review_code CLI/MCP render it too.\n- [ ] RED-first regression tests: test_failclosed_forces_block_on_detector_match asserts verdict[\"blocking\"] non-empty + names the criterion; an adapter-seam test asserts the message never reads \"found 0\".\n- [ ] make lint + code-review suites green; commit carries a rebar-ticket trailer.","id":"f367-3a97-4d74-4cf6","parent_id":"9322-f84a-e047-4471","priority":1,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"BUG: code-review vote renders a DET detector match as 'BLOCK — finding / 0 blocking issues'"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783060803781849001,"uuid":"dab87683-f274-40f6-a9ac-cbfa45cc7b5f"}